{{ja-kanjitab|きみ|yomi=k}}
{{IPAfont|⟨ki<sub>1</sub>mi<sub>1</sub>⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/kʲimʲi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kimi/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=きみ|-}}.

{{ja-noun|きみ}}

# a [[ruler]] of a [[country]]
## an [[emperor]]
##: {{syn|ja|天子|tr=tenshi|天皇|tr2=tennō}}
## a [[lord]]
#: {{ant|ja|臣|tr=omi}}
# a [[master]]
#: {{syn|ja|主君|tr=shukun|主人|tr2=shujin}}
# a [[nobleman]] or other [[person]] of [[high]]([[higher|er]]) [[rank]]
# (''after'' a {{ja-r|が}} ''or'' {{ja-r|の}} ''particle'') ''term of [[respect]] to another [[person]]''
# {{lb|ja|historical|archaic|sort=きみ}} a [[prostitute]]
# {{lb|ja|historical}} one of the [[hereditary]] [[title]]s [[bestow]]ed to [[local]] [[chief]]s in ancient Japan

{{ja-pos|pronoun|きみ|キミ}}

# {{lb|ja|informal|men's speech|sort=きみ}} ''second-person personal pronoun'': [[you]]
